{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id14a7433e-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"842"},"text":"§ 842.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Prohibited acts B","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14a7433f-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Unlawful acts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"It shall be unlawful for any person—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74340-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" who is subject to the requirements of part C to distribute or dispense a controlled substance in violation of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s829"},"text":"section 829 of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74341-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" who is a registrant to distribute or dispense a controlled substance not authorized by his registration to another registrant or other authorized person or to manufacture a controlled substance not authorized by his registration;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74342-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" who is a registrant to distribute a controlled substance in violation of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s825"},"text":"section 825 of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74343-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to remove, alter, or obliterate a symbol or label required by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s825"},"text":"section 825 of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74344-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to refuse or negligently fail to make, keep, or furnish any record, report, notification, declaration, order or order form, statement, invoice, or information required under this subchapter or subchapter II;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74345-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to refuse any entry into any premises or inspection authorized by this subchapter or subchapter II;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74346-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to remove, break, injure, or deface a seal placed upon controlled substances pursuant to section 824(f) or 881 of this title or to remove or dispose of substances so placed under seal;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74347-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to use, to his own advantage, or to reveal, other than to duly authorized officers or employees of the United States, or to the courts when relevant in any judicial proceeding under this subchapter or subchapter II, any information acquired in the course of an inspection authorized by this subchapter concerning any method or process which as a trade secret is entitled to protection, or to use to his own advantage or reveal (other than as authorized by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830"},"text":"section 830 of this title","children":[],"tail":") any information that is confidential under such section;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74348-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" who is a regulated person to engage in a regulated transaction without obtaining the identification required by 830(a)(3) of this title.","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002146"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002146"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/a/3"},"text":"section 830(a)(3) of this title","children":[],"tail":";”."}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74349-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"(10)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" negligently to fail to keep a record or make a report under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830"},"text":"section 830 of this title","children":[],"tail":" or negligently to fail to self-certify as required under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830"},"text":"section 830 of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7434a-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/11"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11"},"text":"(11)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to distribute a laboratory supply to a person who uses, or attempts to use, that laboratory supply to manufacture a controlled substance or a listed chemical, in violation of this subchapter or subchapter II, with reckless disregard for the illegal uses to which such a laboratory supply will be put;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7434b-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/12"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12"},"text":"(12)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" who is a regulated seller, or a distributor required to submit reports under subsection (b)(3) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830"},"text":"section 830 of this title","children":[],"tail":"—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7434c-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/12/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to sell at retail a scheduled listed chemical product in violation of paragraph (1) of subsection (d) of such section, knowing at the time of the transaction involved (independent of consulting the logbook under subsection (e)(1)(A)(iii) of such section) that the transaction is a violation; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7434d-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/12/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to knowingly or recklessly sell at retail such a product in violation of paragraph (2) of such subsection (d);","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7434e-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/13"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"13"},"text":"(13)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" who is a regulated seller to knowingly or recklessly sell at retail a scheduled listed chemical product in violation of subsection (e) of such section;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7434f-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/14"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"14"},"text":"(14)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" who is a regulated seller or an employee or agent of such seller to disclose, in violation of regulations under subparagraph (C) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/e/1"},"text":"section 830(e)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":", information in logbooks under subparagraph (A)(iii) of such section, or to refuse to provide such a logbook to Federal, State, or local law enforcement authorities;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74350-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/15"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"15"},"text":"(15)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to distribute a scheduled listed chemical product to a regulated seller, or to a regulated person referred to in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/b/3/B"},"text":"section 830(b)(3)(B) of this title","children":[],"tail":", unless such regulated seller or regulated person is, at the time of such distribution, currently registered with the Drug Enforcement Administration, or on the list of persons referred to under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/e/1/B/v"},"text":"section 830(e)(1)(B)(v) of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74351-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/16"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"16"},"text":"(16)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to violate subsection (e) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s825"},"text":"section 825 of this title","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002147"},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002147"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74352-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/a/17"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"17"},"text":"(17)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of a registered manufacturer or distributor of opioids, to fail to review the most recent information, directly related to the customers of the manufacturer or distributor, made available by the Attorney General in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s827/f"},"text":"section 827(f) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"As used in paragraph (11), the term “laboratory supply” means a listed chemical or any chemical, substance, or item on a special surveillance list published by the Attorney General, which contains chemicals, products, materials, or equipment used in the manufacture of controlled substances and listed chemicals. For purposes of paragraph (11), there is a rebuttable presumption of reckless disregard at trial if the Attorney General notifies a firm in writing that a laboratory supply sold by the firm, or any other person or firm, has been used by a customer of the notified firm, or distributed further by that customer, for the unlawful production of controlled substances or listed chemicals a firm distributes and 2 weeks or more after the notification the notified firm distributes a laboratory supply to the customer. For purposes of paragraph (15), if the distributor is temporarily unable to access the list of persons referred to under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/e/1/B/v"},"text":"section 830(e)(1)(B)(v) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the distributor may rely on a written, faxed, or electronic copy of a certificate of self-certification submitted by the regulated seller or regulated person, provided the distributor confirms within 7 business days of the distribution that such regulated seller or regulated person is on the list referred to under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/e/1/B/v"},"text":"section 830(e)(1)(B)(v) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14a74353-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Manufacture","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"It shall be unlawful for any person who is a registrant to manufacture a controlled substance in schedule I or II, or ephedrine, pseudoephedrine, or phenylpropanolamine or any of the salts, optical isomers, or salts of optical isomers of such chemical, which is—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74354-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" not expressly authorized by his registration and by a quota assigned to him pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s826"},"text":"section 826 of this title","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74355-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in excess of a quota assigned to him pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s826"},"text":"section 826 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14a74356-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Penalties","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74357-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74358-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in subparagraph (B), (C), or (D) of this paragraph and paragraph (2), any person who violates this section shall, with respect to any such violation, be subject to a civil penalty of not more than $25,000. The district courts of the United States (or, where there is no such court in the case of any territory or possession of the United States, then the court in such territory or possession having the jurisdiction of a district court of the United States in cases arising under the Constitution and laws of the United States) shall have jurisdiction in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1355"},"text":"section 1355 of title 28","children":[],"tail":" to enforce this paragraph."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74359-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id14a7435a-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/1/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in clause (ii), in the case of a violation of paragraph (5), (10), or (17) of subsection (a), the civil penalty shall not exceed $10,000.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id14a7435b-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/1/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In the case of a violation described in clause (i) committed by a registered manufacturer or distributor of opioids and related to the reporting of suspicious orders for opioids, failing to maintain effective controls against diversion of opioids, or failing to review the most recent information made available by the Attorney General in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s827/f"},"text":"section 827(f) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the penalty shall not exceed $100,000."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7435c-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In the case of a violation of paragraph (16) of subsection (a) of this section by an importer, exporter, manufacturer, or distributor (other than as provided in subparagraph (D)), up to $500,000 per violation. For purposes of this subparagraph, a violation is defined as each instance of importation, exportation, manufacturing, distribution, or possession with intent to manufacture or distribute, in violation of paragraph (16) of subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7435d-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In the case of a distribution, dispensing, or possession with intent to distribute or dispense in violation of paragraph (16) of subsection (a) of this section at the retail level, up to $1000 per violation. For purposes of this paragraph, the term “at the retail level” refers to products sold, or held for sale, directly to the consumer for personal use. Each package, container or other separate unit containing an anabolic steroid that is distributed, dispensed, or possessed with intent to distribute or dispense at the retail level in violation of such paragraph (16) of subsection (a) shall be considered a separate violation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7435e-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a7435f-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If a violation of this section is prosecuted by an information or indictment which alleges that the violation was committed knowingly and the trier of fact specifically finds that the violation was so committed, such person shall, except as otherwise provided in subparagraph (B) or (D) of this paragraph, be sentenced to imprisonment of not more than one year or a fine under title 18, or both.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74360-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If a violation referred to in subparagraph (A) was committed after one or more prior convictions of the offender for an offense punishable under this paragraph (2), or for a crime under any other provision of this subchapter or subchapter II or other law of the United States relating to narcotic drugs, marihuana, or depressant or stimulant substances, have become final, such person shall be sentenced to a term of imprisonment of not more than 2 years, a fine under title 18, or both.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74361-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In addition to the penalties set forth elsewhere in this subchapter or subchapter II, any business that violates paragraph (11) of subsection (a) shall, with respect to the first such violation, be subject to a civil penalty of not more than $250,000, but shall not be subject to criminal penalties under this section, and shall, for any succeeding violation, be subject to a civil fine of not more than $250,000 or double the last previously imposed penalty, whichever is greater.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74362-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In the case of a violation described in subparagraph (A) that was a violation of paragraph (5), (10), or (17) of subsection (a) committed by a registered manufacturer or distributor of opioids that relates to the reporting of suspicious orders for opioids, failing to maintain effective controls against diversion of opioids, or failing to review the most recent information made available by the Attorney General in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s827/f"},"text":"section 827(f) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the criminal fine under title 18 shall not exceed $500,000."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74363-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Except under the conditions specified in paragraph (2) of this subsection, a violation of this section does not constitute a crime, and a judgment for the United States and imposition of a civil penalty pursuant to paragraph (1) shall not give rise to any disability or legal disadvantage based on conviction for a criminal offense.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74364-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74365-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If a regulated seller, or a distributor required to submit reports under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/b/3"},"text":"section 830(b)(3) of this title","children":[],"tail":", violates paragraph (12) of subsection (a) of this section, or if a regulated seller violates paragraph (13) of such subsection, the Attorney General may by order prohibit such seller or distributor (as the case may be) from selling any scheduled listed chemical product. Any sale of such a product in violation of such an order is subject to the same penalties as apply under paragraph (2)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14a74366-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s842/c/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An order under subparagraph (A) may be imposed only through the same procedures as apply under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s824/c"},"text":"section 824(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":" for an order to show cause."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id14a74367-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/513/tII/s402"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–513, title II, § 402","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1262"},"text":"84 Stat. 1262","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/633/tII/s202/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–633, title II, § 202(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/3776"},"text":"92 Stat. 3776","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/690/tVI/s6056"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–690, title VI, § 6056","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-18"},"text":"Nov. 18, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/4318"},"text":"102 Stat. 4318","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/237/tII/s205"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–237, title II, § 205","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-03"},"text":"Oct. 3, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3103"},"text":"110 Stat. 3103","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/dA/s101/b/tI/s117"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, div. A, § 101(b) [title I, § 117]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-50"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–50","children":[],"tail":", 2681–68; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dB/tIV/s4002/b/16"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. B, title IV, § 4002(b)(16)","children":[],"tail":", (d)(2)(B), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1808"},"text":"116 Stat. 1808","children":[],"tail":", 1809; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/177/tVII"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–177, title VII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 711(f)(1)(A), (2), 714, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-03-09"},"text":"Mar. 9, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/262-264"},"text":"120 Stat. 262–264","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/268"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–268","children":[],"tail":", §§ 4, 5, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/2847"},"text":"124 Stat. 2847","children":[],"tail":", 2848; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/260/s3/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–260, § 3(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/2931"},"text":"128 Stat. 2931","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/271/tIII/s3273/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–271, title III, § 3273(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-10-24"},"text":"Oct. 24, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/3953"},"text":"132 Stat. 3953","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id14a74368-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id14a74369-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id14a7436a-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s825"},"text":"Section 825 of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in subsec. (a)(16), was so in the original, but probably should have been a reference to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/513/s305"},"text":"section 305 of Pub. L. 91–513","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s825"},"text":"section 825 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Schedules I and II, referred to in subsec. (b), are set out in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s812/c"},"text":"section 812(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id14a7436b-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (a)(17). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/271/s3273/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–271, § 3273(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (17)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/271/s3273/c/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–271, § 3273(c)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (B) and struck out former subpar. (B) which read as follows: “In the case of a violation of paragraph (5) or (10) of subsection (a), the civil penalty shall not exceed $10,000.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/271/s3273/c/2/B/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–271, § 3273(c)(2)(B)(i)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or (D)” after “subparagraph (B)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(D). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/271/s3273/c/2/B/ii"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–271, § 3273(c)(2)(B)(ii)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (D)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (a)(16). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/260/s3/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–260, § 3(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (16)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/260/s3/c/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–260, § 3(c)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, (C), or (D)” after “subparagraph (B)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1)(C), (D). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/260/s3/c/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–260, § 3(c)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added subpars. (C) and (D)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/268/s4/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–268, § 4(4)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “For purposes of paragraph (15), if the distributor is temporarily unable to access the list of persons referred to under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/e/1/B/v"},"text":"section 830(e)(1)(B)(v) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the distributor may rely on a written, faxed, or electronic copy of a certificate of self-certification submitted by the regulated seller or regulated person, provided the distributor confirms within 7 business days of the distribution that such regulated seller or regulated person is on the list referred to under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/e/1/B/v"},"text":"section 830(e)(1)(B)(v) of this title","children":[],"tail":".” at end of concluding provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(10). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/268/s5"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–268, § 5","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or negligently to fail to self-certify as required under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830"},"text":"section 830 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” before semicolon."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(15). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/268/s4/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–268, § 4(1)","children":[],"tail":"–(3), added par. (15)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (a)(12) to (14). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/177/s711/f/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–177, § 711(f)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (12) to (14)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/177/s714"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–177, § 714","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, or ephedrine, pseudoephedrine, or phenylpropanolamine or any of the salts, optical isomers, or salts of optical isomers of such chemical,” after “manufacture a controlled substance in schedule I or II” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/177/s711/f/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–177, § 711(f)(2)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (c)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s4002/d/2/B/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 4002(d)(2)(B)(i)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “under title 18” for “of not more than $25,000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s4002/d/2/B/ii"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 4002(d)(2)(B)(ii)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “under title 18” for “of $50,000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s4002/b/16"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 4002(b)(16)","children":[],"tail":", realigned margins."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—Subsec. (a)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s101/b/tI/s117/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 101(b) [title I, § 117(1)]","children":[],"tail":", inserted “negligently” before “fail”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(10). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s101/b/tI/s117/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 101(b) [title I, § 117(2)]","children":[],"tail":", inserted “negligently” before “to fail”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s101/b/tI/s117/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 101(b) [title I, § 117(3)]","children":[],"tail":", designated existing provisions as subpar. (A), inserted “subparagraph (B) of this paragraph and” before “paragraph (2)”, and added subpar. (B)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/237/s205/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–237, § 205(a)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (11) and closing provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/237/s205/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–237, § 205(b)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (a)(8). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/690/s6056/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–690, § 6056(a)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, or to use to his own advantage or reveal (other than as authorized by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830"},"text":"section 830 of this title","children":[],"tail":") any information that is confidential under such section” after “protection”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(9). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/690/s6056/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–690, § 6056(b)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (9) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (9) read as follows: “to distribute or sell piperidine in violation of regulations established under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s830/a/2"},"text":"section 830(a)(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":", respecting presentation of identification.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(10). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/690/s6056/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–690, § 6056(d)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (10)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","at